*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ First Wall Loads ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
*‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾

f_fw_rad_max = 1.0
* DESCRIPTION:   Radiation wall load peacking factor
* JUSTIFICATION: We consider an average wall load value as a limit

*f_fw_peak = 
* DESCRIPTION:   peaking factor for first wall heat loads. (Applied separately to  (default = 1.0)
*inboard and outboard loads. Applies to both neutron and surface loads. Only used to calculate peak 
*temperature - not the coolant flow rate.) 
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

*icc = 8
* DESCRIPTION:   Neutron wall load upper limit
* JUSTIFICATION: Turned off, dot care about wall load
* VARIABLES:     pflux_fw_neutron_mw calculated in-situ

*i_pflux_fw_neutron = 2
* DESCRIPTION:   Switch for neutron wall load calculation (default = 1)
* =1 use scaled plasma surface area
* =2 use first wall area directly
* JUSTIFICATION: Not set, assuming default value       

*pflux_fw_neutron_max_mw = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Allowable neutron wall-load (MW/m2)
* JUSTIFICATION: Used with icc=8 to enforce wall load limit

*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

icc = 67
* DESCRIPTION:   Upper limit on radiation wall load
* JUSTIFICATION: To avoid melting the first wall
* VARIABLES:     pflux_fw_rad_max_mw calculated in-situ 

pflux_fw_rad_max = 1.2
* DESCRIPTION:   Peak radiation wall load (MW/m^2) 
* JUSTIFICATION: 

*ffwal = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Wall load fiddle factor
* JUSTIFICATION: Not scaling wall load. Used when i_pflux_fw_neutron=1

*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

*icc = 39
* DESCRIPTION:   Constraint equation for first wall temperature upper limit
* JUSTIFICATION: Turned off, do not care about FW temperature
* VARIABLES:     temp_fw_peak (K) calculated in-situ

*temp_fw_max = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Maximum temperature of first wall material [K] (`i_thermal_electric_conversion>1`)(default = 823)
* JUSTIFICATION: Not set as not used

