*---------------------------------Cost-----------------------------------*
*‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾*

* MAJORITY OF COST VARIABLES LEFT OUT DUE TO REMOVAL OF COST MODULES *

output_costs = 1 
* DESCRIPTION:   Switch for Costs Output (1: Write Cost-Related Outputs to File) 
* JUSTIFICATION: Want to see costs

cost_model = 0 
* DESCRIPTION:   Switch for Cost Model 
* JUSTIFICATION: 

*abktflnc = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Allowable FW/Blanket Neutron Fluence (MW-yr/m2)
* JUSTIFICATION: Set to enforce a blanket lifetime (`life_blkt_fpy`) of 5 years

*adivflnc = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Allowable Divertor Heat Fluence (MW-yr/m2)
* JUSTIFICATION: Set to enforce a divertor lifetime (`life_div_fpy`) of 5 years
*                NOTE: not currently functional, issue to be raised

*cpstflnc = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Allowable ST Centrepost Neutron Fluence (MW-yr/m2)
* JUSTIFICATION: Unknown

*fcontng =  
* DESCRIPTION:   Project Contingency Factor
* JUSTIFICATION: 

*fkind =  
* DESCRIPTION:   Multiplier for Nth of a Kind Costs
* JUSTIFICATION: First-of-a-kind reactor

i_bldgs_size = 0
* DESCRIPTION:   Switch between building size estimates (0: Previous work)
* JUSTIFICATION: New model selectable; maintains backwards compatibility

ifueltyp = 0  
* DESCRIPTION:   Switch (0: Treat Blanket, Divertor, FW and CD Equipment as Capital Cost)
* JUSTIFICATION: 

lsa = 2 
* DESCRIPTION:   Level of Safety Assurance Switch (2: In-Between)
* JUSTIFICATION: 

*________________________________________________________________________*
*---------------------------------Vacuum---------------------------------*
*‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾*

* Calculates pumping rates and required pumps*

*i_vacuum_pumping = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Switch for vacuum pumping model:
* ='old' for old detailed ETR model
* ='simple' for simple steady-state model with comparison to ITER cryopumps
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*i_vacuum_pump_type = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Switch for vacuum pump type:
* =0 - for turbomolecular pump (magnetic bearing) with speed of 2.0 m3/s
*    (1.95 for N2, 1.8 for He, 1.8 for DT)
* =1 - for compound cryopump with nominal speed of 10.0 m3/s
*  (9.0 for N2, 5.0 for He and 25.0 for DT)
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*pres_vv_chamber_base = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Base pressure during dwell before gas pre-fill (Pa):
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*pres_div_chamber_burn = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Divertor chamber pressure during burn (Pa):
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*molflow_vac_pumps = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Pump throughput (molecules/s) (default is ITER value) (default = 1.2155e+22) :
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*outgrat_fw = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Plasma chamber wall outgassing rate (Pa-m/s) (default = 1.3D-8) :
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*temp_vv_chamber_gas_burn_end = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Neutral gas temperature in chamber (K) (default = 300) :
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*i_vac_pump_dwell = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Switch for dwell pumping options:
* =0 pumping only during t_plant_pulse_dwell
* =1 pumping only during t_plant_pulse_coil_precharge
* =2 pumping during t_plant_pulse_dwell + t_plant_pulse_coil_precharge
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*pumpareafraction = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Area of one pumping port as a fraction of plasma surface area (default = 0.0203) :
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*volflow_vac_pumps_max = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Maximum pumping speed per unit area for deuterium & tritium, molecular flow (default = 27.3) :
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*pres_vv_chamber_dwell_start = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Initial neutral pressure at the beginning of the dwell phase (Pa) (default = 1.0) :
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*f_volflow_vac_pumps_impedance = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Effective pumping speed reduction factor due to duct impedance (default = 0.167) :
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*outgasindex = 
* DESCRIPTION:   Outgassing decay index (default = 1.0) :
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*outgasfactor = 
* DESCRIPTION:   outgassing prefactor kw: outgassing rate at 1 s per unit area (Pa m s-1) (default = 0.0235) :
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set.

*icc = 63
* DESCRIPTION:   Upper limit on n_iter_vacuum_pumps (i_vacuum_pumping = simple)
* JUSTIFICATION: Turned off, not using simple pumping 
* VARIABLES:     tfno(TF coil number), n_iter_vacuum_pumps calculated in-situ

*________________________________________________________________________*
*---------------------------------Time-----------------------------------*
*‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾*

i_pulsed_plant = 0
* DESCRIPTION:   i_pulsed_plant = 1 pulsed machine. i_pulsed_plant = 0 steady state machine
* JUSTIFICATION: Default is steady state machine

*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

*icc = 13
* DESCRIPTION:   Constraint for burn time lower limit
* JUSTIFICATION: Not used, no minimum burn time required
* VARIABLES:     Calculated in-situ

*t_burn_min =  
* DESCRIPTION:   Minimum required burn Time (s)
* JUSTIFICATION: No required burn time

t_plant_pulse_burn = 1000.0 
* DESCRIPTION:   Burn Time (s)
* JUSTIFICATION: Default, steady-state device so input, calculates if i_pulsed_plant = 1

*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

t_plant_pulse_dwell = 100.0 
* DESCRIPTION:   Time Between Pulses in a Pulsed Reactor (s)
* JUSTIFICATION: Steady-state device, assumed

*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

*pulsetimings
* DESCRIPTION:   Switch for pulse timings (if i_pulsed_plant=1):
* =0, t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_up = Ip(MA)/0.1 t_plant_pulse_coil_precharge, t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_down = input
* =1, t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_up = iteration var or input. t_plant_pulse_coil_precharge/t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_down max of input or t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_up
* JUSTIFICATION: Assuming default, may change

*icc = 41
* DESCRIPTION:   Constraint equation for plasma current ramp-up time lower limit
* JUSTIFICATION: Turned off, do not care about plasma current ramp up time 
* VARIABLES:     t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_up (s) calculated in-situ

*t_current_ramp_up_min =  
* DESCRIPTION:   Minimum plasma current ramp-up time (s)
* JUSTIFICATION: Turned off, not using icc = 41

*tohsin =  
* DESCRIPTION:   Switch for t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_up calculation
* = 0, t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_up = t_plant_pulse_coil_precharge = t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_down = Ip(MA)/0.5
* = 1, t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_up = tohsin; t_plant_pulse_coil_precharge, t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_down are input
* JUSTIFICATION: Not used, assuming default

*t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_down =  
* DESCRIPTION:   PF coil shutdown time (s)
* JUSTIFICATION: Assuming default.

*t_plant_pulse_plasma_current_ramp_up =  
* DESCRIPTION:   Plasma current ramp-up time for current initiation (s)
* JUSTIFICATION: Assuming default of 10 seconds

*t_plant_pulse_coil_precharge =  
* DESCRIPTION:   Initial charge time for PF coils (s)
* JUSTIFICATION: Assuming default.

*theat =  
* DESCRIPTION:   Heating time after current ramp (s)
* JUSTIFICATION: Assuming default of 10 seconds

*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

*icc = 42
* DESCRIPTION:   Constraint equation for full pulse cycle time lower limit. 
* JUSTIFICATION: Turned off, do not care about the full pulse cycle time 
* VARIABLES:     t_plant_pulse_total (s) calculated in-situ

*t_cycle_min =  
* DESCRIPTION:   Minimum full pulse cycle time (s)
* JUSTIFICATION: Turned off, not using icc = 42

*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


