*i_pf_energy_storage_source = 
* DESCRIPTION:    Switch for PF coil energy storage option (default = 2):
* =1 all power from MGF (motor-generator flywheel) units
* =2 all pulsed power from line
* =3 PF power from MGF, heating from line
*(In fact, options 1 and 3 are not treated differently)
* JUSTIFICATION: Not yet set

*icc = 66
* DESCRIPTION:   Limit on rate of change of energy in poloidal field
* JUSTIFICATION: Turned off, don't care about poloidal field change
* VARIABLES:     maxpoloidalpower (Maximum permitted absolute rate of change of stored energy in poloidal field (MW)), peakpoloidalpower calculated in-situ

*maxpoloidalpower = 
* DESCRIPTION:    Maximum permitted absolute rate of change of stored energy in poloidal field (MW)
* JUSTIFICATION: Not set as not using icc = 66

*etapsu =  
* DESCRIPTION:   Efficiency of transfer of PF stored energy into or out of storage.
* JUSTIFICATION: Not used. Using default

*~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

*istore =  
* DESCRIPTION:   Switch for thermal storage method: (default = 1)
* =1 option 1 of Electrowatt report, AEA FUS 205
* =2 option 2 of Electrowatt report, AEA FUS 205
* =3 stainless steel block
* JUSTIFICATION: Not used. Using default

*dtstor =  
* DESCRIPTION:   Maximum allowable temperature change in stainless steel thermal storage 
* block (K) (`istore=3`) (default = 300.0)
* JUSTIFICATION: Not used. Using default

